Teile dieses Profils können maschinell übersetzt werden. Die Übersetzung kann Fehler enthalten.          Übersetzung anzeigen.Original anzeigen.AblehnenAlex MandlDirector of Regional OperationsStandortBrooklyn, New YorkBrancheGesundheit, Wellness & FitnessAktuellIora Health, Harken HealthFrüherEmblemHealth, NYC Department of Small Business Services, Structured Employment Economic Development CorporationAusbildungHarvard Business SchoolEmpfehlungen1 Person hat Alex Mandl empfohlen418 KontakteSehen Sie sich Alex Mandls vollständiges Profil an. Es ist kostenlos.Ihre Kollegen, Kommilitonen und 500 Millionen weitere Fach- und Führungskräfte sind bereits auf LinkedIn.Alex Mandls vollständiges Profil anzeigenAlex Mandls AktivitätenIs it time for your LinkedIn Makeover?Alex Mandl gefällt Folgendes:ZusammenfassungHealthcare InnovatorMy aim is to make healthcare more effective, more affordable, and more responsive to individual needs. Too many people are lost in a maze of providers, prescriptions, and product density, searching for common sense and clarity. I’ve worked behind the scenes and on the ground to enhance coordination and collaboration. And I’ve seen firsthand how new approaches to care can improve outcomes and experiences.  Dynamic LeaderI’ve built and managed teams, overhauled systems and processes, and guided people and projects through intense challenges and complexity. My experience has spanned many different functions and I am comfortable working in both entrepreneurial settings and established organizations. I appreciate the need for balance and flexibility, especially while applying innovation to deeply rooted practices.   Change AgentI have a keen appreciation for laying groundwork and achieving support for new methods and possibilities. At every step, I make sure people know and feel that they are valued for their input, not just their output. I also have a strong capacity to frame and sequence work so that the different components come together in a productive and sustainable manner.  Relationship BuilderI thrive on forging connections both within organizations and beyond. I make a point of getting to know people, understanding what drives them and what they are looking to achieve. I integrate different perspectives while creating consensus around specific strategies and actions. And I enjoy working with people of all backgrounds and levels of experience to develop and implement creative ideas.  Grounded VisionaryGiven the rapid and turbulent change in healthcare, strong leadership is required to provide vision, build foundations, and consolidate progress. I offer fresh thinking combined with practical strategies to achieve tangible results.ErfahrungDirector of Regional OperationsIora HealthOktober 2015  –  Heute (1 Jahr 10 Monate)Großraum Chicago und UmgebungI joined Iora for the opportunity to create a seamless Care + Insurance model with Harken Health (a newly formed subsidiary of UnitedHealthCare). We use relationship-based primary care to engage patients, coordinate care, improve outcomes, and reduce unnecessary costs. Launching Partnerships I relocated from New York to set up four primary care centers in Chicago, complete with new teams, new products, new facilities, a new brand, and a new organization.  My efforts entail significant coordination between Harken Centers in Chicago and Atlanta, Harken HQ in Minnetonka, and Iora HQ in Boston. Developing WorkflowsI am responsible for management, operations, and performance across the Chicago market. I routinely work through challenges with systems, processes, people, and strategies. My efforts focus largely on the following:•	Clarifying roles, responsibilities, and expectations•	Identifying priorities and marshaling resources to address them •	Bolstering connectivity among different functions and locationsCollaborating with ProvidersI work closely with providers to solve complex problems and adapt strategies. I help them balance the demands of daily operations with the need to drive clinical innovation. Topics include: •	Supporting development of provider leadership & management skills•	Focusing attention on metrics and fine tuning methods to improve performance•	Population health management, patient education and empowerment•	Enhancing coordination of care with specialists / hospitalsBuilding Strong TeamsI spend significant time on the ground to ensure that I fully understand different contexts and perspectives. Key efforts include:  •	Hiring, training, and developing team members at every level•	Promoting adaptability in the face of rapidly shifting dynamics•	Engaging leaders in tough conversations about performance and strategic challenges•	Fostering a culture where teamwork, creativity, and perseverance thriveDirector of Regional OperationsHarken HealthOktober 2015  –  Heute (1 Jahr 10 Monate)Großraum Chicago und UmgebungEmployee Engagement Leader and Communications StrategistEmblemHealth2011  –  2014 (3 Jahre)Großraum New York City und UmgebungHelped employees across the company adopt new behaviors and perspectives to support evolution of a more consumer focused brand. Promoted understanding and ownership of major initiatives such as Health Care Reform, Medicare Stars, and other efforts to increase member satisfaction. Coordinated internal brand campaigns and developed new opportunities for cross functional collaboration. Senior Advisor and Implementation ManagerNYC Department of Small Business Services2006  –  2010 (4 Jahre)Played a key role in the transformation of NYC Workforce1 Career Centers.  Worked across a wide range of systems, policies, operations, and personnel to revolutionize customer experiences for jobseekers and employers.  Negotiated with city and state government officials to foster common understanding and joint action on complex issues.  Managed a broad portfolio of issues including eligibility, compliance, training, data systems, process improvement, and strategy.Strategic Operations CoordinatorStructured Employment Economic Development Corporation2004  –  2006 (2 Jahre)Provided strategic advice and hands on assistance to improve performance in non-profit organizations.  Reconfigured operations at the NYC Workforce1 Career Center in Upper Manhattan.  Observed and adjusted workflow, resource allocation, and other tactical areas.  Measured performance and worked closely with front line staff to understand, illustrate, and solve problems.  Collaborated with peers in other career centers to tackle system-wide issues and implement best practices.Consultant and Freelance WriterIndependent2002  –  2003 (1 Jahr)Co-authored "The Philanthropic Response to 9/11" - a report commissioned by Simpson Thatcher Bartlett LLP and supported by the Carnegie Corporation to explore and publish best practices in coordination of relief in response to large scale disasters.  Interviewed senior leaders in government agencies and non-profit organizations and compiled their thoughts and observations into comprehensive and articulate findings and recommendations.Special Assistant for Logistics ManagementU.S. Department of State1998  –  2000 (2 Jahre)Washington D.C. Metro und UmgebungRotated among many different divisions of the newly created Office of Logistics Management.  Learned the skills, functions, and challenges of each area (e.g. Warehousing, Procurement, Transportation).  Earned the trust and respect of division leaders by taking on entrenched problems and communicating issues frankly and clearly.  Reported directly to the Deputy Assistant Secretary, who ensured a diverse management training experience.Staff Assistant for Presidential PersonnelThe White House1997  –  1998 (1 Jahr)Washington D.C. Metro und UmgebungSupported fast, efficient, and accurate filling of vacancies across all cabinet agencies.  Worked with liaisons in each department (e.g. Defense, Education, State, Treasury) to ensure that their needs were well understood and met quickly.  Created new systems for filing and classifying candidates.  Collaborated with many other internal offices throughout the White House to understand and communicate their needs and perspectives to senior officials.dummy1dummy2Original anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenKenntnissePolicyGeschäftsführungLeadershipProgrammmanagementProgram ManagementStrategisches ManagementStrategyProzessverbesserungProcess ImprovementAbteilungsübergreifende TeamführungCross-functional Team LeadershipNon-Profit-OrganisationenNonprofitsSocial MediaWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!AusbildungHarvard Business SchoolMaster of Business Administration (MBA), Organizational Development, Operations ManagementMaster of Business Administration (MBA), Organizational Development, Operations Management2000  –  2002UclaUCLAOriginal anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!Bachelor's degree, VerlaufBachelor's degree, HistoryOriginal anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!1992  –  1996Universität von ExeterUniversity of ExeterOriginal anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!Junior Year Abroad, VerlaufJunior Year Abroad, HistoryOriginal anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!1994  –  1995EhrenamtVolontär ConsultantVolunteer ConsultantOriginal anzeigenÜbersetzung anzeigenWie finden Sie diese Übersetzung?Gut•FehlerhaftDanke für Ihre Hilfe!HBS Community Partners2010  –  Heute (7 Jahre)GesundheitCoordinate pro-bono consulting projects for groups of HBS alumni to help nonprofit organizations with strategic challenges.  Projects typically include organizational development, marketing, strategic planning, and financial diversification.  Themen, die Alex Mandl wichtig sind:TierschutzAusbildungUmweltGesundheitPolitikEmpfehlungenHier ein kleiner Vorgeschmack darauf, was LinkedIn Mitglieder über Alex