Alex MandlDirector of Regional OperationsLocationBrooklyn, New YorkIndustryHealth, Wellness and FitnessCurrentIora Health, Harken HealthPreviousEmblemHealth, NYC Department of Small Business Services, Structured Employment Economic Development CorporationEducationHarvard Business SchoolRecommendations1 person has recommended Alex418 connectionsView Alex’s full profile. It's free!Your colleagues, classmates, and 500 million other professionals are on LinkedIn.View Alex’s Full ProfileAlex’s ActivityIs it time for your LinkedIn Makeover?Alex likedSummaryHealthcare InnovatorMy aim is to make healthcare more effective, more affordable, and more responsive to individual needs. Too many people are lost in a maze of providers, prescriptions, and product density, searching for common sense and clarity. I’ve worked behind the scenes and on the ground to enhance coordination and collaboration. And I’ve seen firsthand how new approaches to care can improve outcomes and experiences.  Dynamic LeaderI’ve built and managed teams, overhauled systems and processes, and guided people and projects through intense challenges and complexity. My experience has spanned many different functions and I am comfortable working in both entrepreneurial settings and established organizations. I appreciate the need for balance and flexibility, especially while applying innovation to deeply rooted practices.   Change AgentI have a keen appreciation for laying groundwork and achieving support for new methods and possibilities. At every step, I make sure people know and feel that they are valued for their input, not just their output. I also have a strong capacity to frame and sequence work so that the different components come together in a productive and sustainable manner.  Relationship BuilderI thrive on forging connections both within organizations and beyond. I make a point of getting to know people, understanding what drives them and what they are looking to achieve. I integrate different perspectives while creating consensus around specific strategies and actions. And I enjoy working with people of all backgrounds and levels of experience to develop and implement creative ideas.  Grounded VisionaryGiven the rapid and turbulent change in healthcare, strong leadership is required to provide vision, build foundations, and consolidate progress. I offer fresh thinking combined with practical strategies to achieve tangible results.ExperienceDirector of Regional OperationsIora HealthOctober 2015  –  Present (1 year 10 months)Greater Chicago AreaI joined Iora for the opportunity to create a seamless Care + Insurance model with Harken Health (a newly formed subsidiary of UnitedHealthCare). We use relationship-based primary care to engage patients, coordinate care, improve outcomes, and reduce unnecessary costs. Launching Partnerships I relocated from New York to set up four primary care centers in Chicago, complete with new teams, new products, new facilities, a new brand, and a new organization.  My efforts entail significant coordination between Harken Centers in Chicago and Atlanta, Harken HQ in Minnetonka, and Iora HQ in Boston. Developing WorkflowsI am responsible for management, operations, and performance across the Chicago market. I routinely work through challenges with systems, processes, people, and strategies. My efforts focus largely on the following:•	Clarifying roles, responsibilities, and expectations•	Identifying priorities and marshaling resources to address them •	Bolstering connectivity among different functions and locationsCollaborating with ProvidersI work closely with providers to solve complex problems and adapt strategies. I help them balance the demands of daily operations with the need to drive clinical innovation. Topics include: •	Supporting development of provider leadership & management skills•	Focusing attention on metrics and fine tuning methods to improve performance•	Population health management, patient education and empowerment•	Enhancing coordination of care with specialists / hospitalsBuilding Strong TeamsI spend significant time on the ground to ensure that I fully understand different contexts and perspectives. Key efforts include:  •	Hiring, training, and developing team members at every level•	Promoting adaptability in the face of rapidly shifting dynamics•	Engaging leaders in tough conversations about performance and strategic challenges•	Fostering a culture where teamwork, creativity, and perseverance thriveDirector of Regional OperationsHarken HealthOctober 2015  –  Present (1 year 10 months)Greater Chicago AreaEmployee Engagement Leader and Communications StrategistEmblemHealth2011  –  2014 (3 years)Greater New York City AreaHelped employees across the company adopt new behaviors and perspectives to support evolution of a more consumer focused brand. Promoted understanding and ownership of major initiatives such as Health Care Reform, Medicare Stars, and other efforts to increase member satisfaction. Coordinated internal brand campaigns and developed new opportunities for cross functional collaboration. Senior Advisor and Implementation ManagerNYC Department of Small Business Services2006  –  2010 (4 years)Played a key role in the transformation of NYC Workforce1 Career Centers.  Worked across a wide range of systems, policies, operations, and personnel to revolutionize customer experiences for jobseekers and employers.  Negotiated with city and state government officials to foster common understanding and joint action on complex issues.  Managed a broad portfolio of issues including eligibility, compliance, training, data systems, process improvement, and strategy.Strategic Operations CoordinatorStructured Employment Economic Development Corporation2004  –  2006 (2 years)Provided strategic advice and hands on assistance to improve performance in non-profit organizations.  Reconfigured operations at the NYC Workforce1 Career Center in Upper Manhattan.  Observed and adjusted wo